6. Explain Angular Authentication and Authorization.\par
The user login credentials are passed to an authenticated API, which is present\par
on the server. Post-server-side validation of the credentials, a JWT (JSON Web\par
Token) is returned. The JWT has information or attributes regarding the current\par
user. The user is then identified with the given JWT. This is called authentication.\par
\par
Post-logging-in successfully, different users have a different level of access. While some may access everything, access for others might be restricted to only some resources. The level of access is authorization.\par
