7. Can you explain the concept of scope hierarchy in Angular?\par
Angular organizes the $scope objects into a hierarchy that is typically used by \par
views. This is known as the scope hierarchy in Angular. It has a root scope that\par
can further contain one or several scopes called child scopes.\par
\par
In a scope hierarchy, each view has its own $scope. Hence, the variables set by\par
a view\rquote s view controller will remain hidden to other view controllers. \f0\par
